
Overview of noun drain

The noun drain has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (1) drain, drainage -- (emptying something accomplished by allowing liquid to run out of it)
2. drain -- (tube inserted into a body cavity (as during surgery) to remove unwanted material)
3. drain, drainpipe, waste pipe -- (a pipe through which liquid is carried away)
4. drain -- (a gradual depletion of energy or resources; "a drain on resources"; "a drain of young talent by emigration")

Overview of verb drain

The verb drain has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (2) drain, run out -- (flow off gradually; "The rain water drains into this big vat")
2. (1) drain -- (deplete of resources; "The exercise class drains me of energy")
3. (1) drain -- (empty of liquid; drain the liquid from; "We drained the oil tank")
4. enfeeble, debilitate, drain -- (make weak; "Life in the camp drained him")
